body:
@masterkain bulk alter table was introduced for the "mysql" gem, but for whatever reason this originally didn't extend to the "mysql2" gem, which is quite popular. 

This patch was to extend that capability to mysql2. I wasn't able to put the common mysql code into an abstract mysql adapter for whatever reason and this was a quick fix.

@joelmichael bulk altering should work for mysql and mysql2 gems as of the following changeset thanks to @jonleighton 

https://github.com/rails/rails/commit/fd22d040fef48778a519825dd2f0cf2fd73a8965#activerecord/lib/active_record/connection_adapters/abstract_mysql_adapter.rb

I am therefore closing this Pull Request.
